			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To the poster who said STR was useless to a mage, I dont know what your strength is, but my base is 55, and right now it is 70 with focus items and the odd item here and there that adds str.  I carry an archeologist pack, and 2 backpacks and i get encumbered even looking at a warrior.  In looking at all the apothic gear, I count 37 int from this gear alone (full set).  Now add that to the int items that you already have and your base int, and 200 int is so easy it is unreal.  Now, what do you do with all those extra slots?  well you start boosting other stats.  Me since im always playing the encumberance game (coin is the worst offender) str is something i would look for.  I replaced a +4 int ring with a moonstone ring (+3 str +30 mana) and let me tell you, the str helps...  i also find myself holding my shovel of ponz a lot to help with the str, and i also have some bone arm plates (+5 str -4 dex) that i use when on a long camp with lots of coin being dropped.<BR>
<BR>
Even though you are a caster, that dosent mean that any one stat is useless. Every stat plays a part in the grand scheme of things. <BR>
<BR>
Pensy Stormbringer<BR>
40 Magician <BR>
Luclin
